				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="恋愛禁止学園 (Renai Kinshi Gakuen)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#230;&amp;#129;&amp;#139;&amp;#230;&amp;#132;&amp;#155;&amp;#231;&amp;#166;&amp;#129;&amp;#230;&amp;#173;&amp;#162;&amp;#229;&amp;#173;&amp;#166;&amp;#229;&amp;#156;&amp;#146; (Renai Kinshi Gakuen) is a hidden identity game from Japan. 'Gakuen' is high school, and 'Ren-aikinshi' is the rule talent agencies apply to their stars forbidding personal relationships (because they think it deters the fans). So the game tile means a love-ban at high school. In this game, a player must find the one they are destined to fall in love with. The player count is 5 to 9, because of the minimum five roles in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Set in a school where romance is prohibited, the goal is to fulfill the love between the main character and the destined person. However, if the disciplinary committee among the students finds out about the relationship, there is a danger of expulsion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players have five roles:&amp;#10;1. Protagonist looking for a destined person&amp;#10;2. A person destined to do his best to be confessed to by the main character&amp;#10;3. A friend who supports the main character and the destined person&amp;#10;4. If confessed to by the main character, the only rival&amp;#10;5. A disciplinary committee member who finds the person of destiny and expels him from school&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Only the main character's role is revealed, and the identity of the other players is unknown.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Using the prepared character cards and combination attribute cards, you will play a role and perform events that are common in school things. Even if you know the other player's identity, the only way to tell it to the main character is through role-playing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Depending on their role, each player has a different win condition.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An expansion pack was published later.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
